  "prompt": "Do the construction companies offer training to their freshers?",
  "response": "Yes, many construction companies offer training programs for their freshers. These programs are designed to help new employees develop the skills and knowledge necessary to excel in the construction industry. Training for freshers can include a mix of on-the-job training, mentorship, safety training, technical skills development, and sometimes classroom-based learning. The specifics of the training can vary widely depending on the company, the job role, and the complexity of the projects they handle.\n\nSome companies may also partner with vocational schools or offer apprenticeships that combine formal education with practical experience. This approach not only helps new employees become productive more quickly but also ensures that they adhere to the company\u2019s standards and practices.",
